## Requirements Flow (/dx-req-all)

**Developer types:** `/dx-req-all <ADO-Story-ID>` (or individual skills: `/dx-req-fetch`, `/dx-req-dor`, etc.)

Chains 5 skills sequentially via `dx-step-executor` agents. Each step must complete before the next starts.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    ADO_ID["ADO Story ID"]

    subgraph S1["Step 1"]
        FETCH["/dx-req-fetch<br/>Fetch story, create<br/>spec dir and branch"]
        RAW["raw-story.md<br/>.branch, .sprint"]
        FETCH --> RAW
    end

    subgraph S2["Step 2"]
        DOR["/dx-req-dor<br/>Validate readiness,<br/>post checklist to ADO"]
        DOR_OUT["dor-report.md<br/>+ ADO comment"]
        DOR --> DOR_OUT
    end

    subgraph S3["Step 3"]
        EXPLAIN["/dx-req-explain<br/>Distill story into<br/>8-12 dev requirements"]
        EXPLAIN_OUT["explain.md"]
        EXPLAIN --> EXPLAIN_OUT
    end

    subgraph S4["Step 4"]
        RESEARCH["/dx-req-research<br/>Search codebase with<br/>4 parallel Explore agents"]
        RESEARCH_OUT["research.md"]
        RESEARCH --> RESEARCH_OUT
    end

    subgraph S5["Step 5"]
        SHARE["/dx-req-share<br/>Plain-language summary<br/>for team and BA"]
        SHARE_OUT["share-plan.md<br/>+ ADO comment"]
        SHARE --> SHARE_OUT
    end

    ADO_ID --> FETCH
    RAW --> DOR
    DOR_OUT -->|"GATE: no blocking questions"| EXPLAIN
    EXPLAIN_OUT --> RESEARCH
    RESEARCH_OUT --> SHARE

    style S1 fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style S2 fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style S3 fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style S4 fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style S5 fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style DOR fill:#bbdefb,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    style SHARE fill:#bbdefb,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
```

**Idempotent:** Each skill checks if its output file exists and is current before regenerating. Re-running skips up-to-date files.

