## Planning Flow (/dx-plan)

**Developer types:** `/dx-plan <ADO-Story-ID>`

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph INPUTS["Input Files (created by /dx-req-all + /dx-figma-*)"]
        EXP["explain.md (required)"]
        RES["research.md (recommended)"]
        RAW["raw-story.md (reference)"]
        CONV["figma-conventions.md (optional)"]
        PROTO_IN["prototype/ (optional)"]
    end

    subgraph PLANNING["Planning"]
        PLAN["/dx-plan<br/>Reason about dependencies,<br/>order, and file changes"]
        IMPL["implement.md<br/>Steps with Status: pending"]
        PLAN --> IMPL
    end

    subgraph VALIDATION["Validation"]
        VAL["/dx-plan-validate<br/>Check: requirement coverage,<br/>scope creep, dependency order,<br/>file existence, tests, reuse"]
        VERDICT{Verdict}
        RESOLVE["/dx-plan-resolve<br/>Search codebase for solutions,<br/>patch implement.md"]
        VAL --> VERDICT
        VERDICT -->|"PASS"| READY((Plan Ready))
        VERDICT -->|"FAIL or WARNINGS"| RESOLVE
        RESOLVE --> VAL
    end

    EXP --> PLAN
    RES --> PLAN
    RAW -.-> PLAN
    CONV -.-> PLAN
    PROTO_IN -.-> PLAN
    IMPL --> VAL

    style PLANNING fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style VALIDATION fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
```

**Note:** `/dx-plan-validate` does NOT modify `implement.md` -- it only reports. `/dx-plan-resolve` reads the validation output and applies fixes to `implement.md`.

