## Implementation Flow (/dx-step-all)

**Developer types:** `/dx-step-all <ADO-Story-ID>` (or `/dx-step` to execute one step at a time)

Loops through each pending step in `implement.md`. All steps are strictly sequential.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    IMPL["implement.md<br/>(created by /dx-plan)"]

    subgraph LOOP["Per-Step Loop"]
        direction TB
        PICK["Pick next pending step"]
        CODE["2a /dx-step<br/>Write code for one<br/>plan step"]
        TEST["2b /dx-step-test<br/>Run project test suite"]
        REVIEW["2c /dx-step-review<br/>AI code review against<br/>plan and conventions"]
        FIX["2d /dx-step-fix<br/>Diagnose failure,<br/>apply correction"]
        HEAL["2d-heal /dx-step-heal<br/>Root-cause analysis,<br/>insert corrective steps"]
        COMMIT_S["2e /dx-step-commit<br/>Git commit with<br/>work item link"]

        PICK --> CODE --> TEST
        TEST -->|pass| REVIEW
        TEST -->|fail| FIX
        REVIEW -->|pass| COMMIT_S
        REVIEW -->|changes requested| FIX
        FIX -->|"fixed, attempt 1-2"| TEST
        FIX -->|"failed 2x"| HEAL
        HEAL -->|"healed, new steps"| PICK
        HEAL -->|"unrecoverable after 2 cycles"| STOP((STOP))
        COMMIT_S -->|"more pending"| PICK
        COMMIT_S -->|"all done"| DONE((All Steps Done))
    end

    IMPL --> PICK

    LEARNING["Learning System<br/>runs.jsonl, fixes.jsonl<br/>Auto-promote to rules after 3+ successes"]
    DONE --> LEARNING

    style LOOP fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style CODE fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
    style FIX fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
    style HEAL fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
    style COMMIT_S fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
```

**Fix rules:** Max 2 consecutive fix attempts per step, then heal. Max 2 healing cycles per original step, then STOP.

