## PR Flow (/dx-pr)

**Developer types:** `/dx-pr <ADO-Story-ID>` or `/dx-pr-commit`

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph CREATE["PR Creation (/dx-pr)"]
        PR_CMD["/dx-pr<br/>Create pull request<br/>from completed plan"]
        CHECK_STEPS["Verify ALL implement.md steps<br/>are Status: done"]
        PUSH["Push branch with -u<br/>to remote"]
        CREATE_PR["Create ADO PR<br/>Auto-link work item"]
        PR_CMD --> CHECK_STEPS
        CHECK_STEPS -->|"all done"| PUSH --> CREATE_PR
        CHECK_STEPS -->|"incomplete"| BLOCKED((Blocked))
    end

    style CREATE fill:none,stroke:#90a4ae
    style CREATE_PR fill:#e1bee7,stroke:#6a1b9a,color:#000
```

### Reviewing Others' PRs (separate lifecycle)

**Developer types:** `/dx-pr-review <PR-URL>`

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    PR_REVIEW["/dx-pr-review<br/>Spawn dx-pr-reviewer agent<br/>to analyze PR diff"]
    FIRST{"First review<br/>or follow-up?"}
    FIRST_R["Analyze full diff,<br/>save findings to<br/>pr-ID-findings.md"]
    FOLLOWUP_R["Compare old vs new commits,<br/>classify: FIXED / ARGUED / IGNORED"]
    PATCHES["Generate fix patches<br/>via worktree agent<br/>(user chooses)"]
    POST_INLINE["Post review comments<br/>to ADO threads"]
    VOTE["Set vote: Approve /<br/>Approve with suggestions /<br/>Changes requested"]

    PR_REVIEW --> FIRST
    FIRST -->|first| FIRST_R
    FIRST -->|"session exists"| FOLLOWUP_R
    FIRST_R --> PATCHES --> POST_INLINE --> VOTE

    style POST_INLINE fill:#e1bee7,stroke:#6a1b9a,color:#000
    style VOTE fill:#e1bee7,stroke:#6a1b9a,color:#000
```

**Note:** Posting happens inline within `/dx-pr-review` (Step 8) — it does NOT call `/dx-pr-post`. The standalone `/dx-pr-post` skill is only for deferred posting of previously saved findings.

### Handling Feedback on Your PR (separate lifecycle)

**Developer types:** `/dx-pr-answer <PR-URL>`

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    ANSWER["/dx-pr-answer<br/>Research codebase context,<br/>draft replies to open threads"]
    CATEGORIZE["Categorize each thread:<br/>agree-will-fix / question /<br/>disagree / skip"]
    DETECT["Detect proposed patches<br/>in reviewer comments"]
    POST_REPLIES["Post approved replies<br/>to ADO threads"]
    FIX_PR["/dx-pr-fix<br/>Apply agree-will-fix changes,<br/>lint, commit, push"]
    REPLY_FIXED["Reply to fixed threads:<br/>Fixed. / Updated."]

    ANSWER --> CATEGORIZE --> DETECT --> POST_REPLIES
    POST_REPLIES -->|"agree-will-fix threads exist"| FIX_PR --> REPLY_FIXED

    style POST_REPLIES fill:#e1bee7,stroke:#6a1b9a,color:#000
    style FIX_PR fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
    style REPLY_FIXED fill:#e1bee7,stroke:#6a1b9a,color:#000
```

### Standalone PR-Related Skills

- **`/dx-pr-commit`** — Alternative to `/dx-pr`: commit + create PR in one command
- **`/dx-pr-post`** — Post previously saved review findings to ADO (deferred posting)
- **`/dx-doc-gen`** — Generate wiki page from spec files, post to ADO wiki
- **`/dx-req-dod`** — Check Definition of Done: PR approved? Tasks done?

**Key:** Three independent lifecycles — PR creation, reviewing others' PRs, and handling feedback on your own PR. `/dx-pr-commit` is an alternative to `/dx-pr`.

